race.comment: Siding with TEMPRANILLO (7) off a strong maiden win at Kilmore, backed into $2.20 there and coming from back in the field to score. The pace was strong there and it resulted in a good time, giving an ideal platform to go to 1600m now which should only suit her better. She'll likely concede a start again but can measure up. ENCHANTED JENNI (3) has won her past two nicely, putting away five rivals comfortably at Cranbourne last time. She's struck some form and can go right on with it. EMPIRE OF PAIN (2) was good in a stronger race at Flemington last time and looks well placed back to this level. SIRENA (4) maps nicely and can peak third up.
